definition: one after the other/in single file
to pierce through/to pass through/to be stringed together/string of 1000 cash
to walk in in a line
to file out/to walk out in a line

sentences.english: We filed out to the accompaniment of the organ.
sentences.chinese: 我們在管風琴伴奏下魚貫而出。

sentences.english: By the time the dignitaries had filed out, it was too late.
sentences.chinese: 當這些高官顯貴魚貫而出之後，一切都太晚了。

sentences.english: The students filed in the classroom.
The bell rang and out rushed the children.
The jury filed out of the courtroom.
sentences.chinese: 陪審員們從法庭裏魚貫而出。

sentences.english: A group of students filed in, fourteen or fifteen all told.
sentences.chinese: 一隊學生魚貫而入，共有十四五個人。

sentences.english: The students filed into the classroom.
Hearing the sound of the engine, passengers file in the bus. And the cicerone does the nose-count again.
sentences.chinese: 聽到車子發動的聲音，旅客們又魚貫而入了。

sentences.english: As 409 students filed out of their exam.
sentences.chinese: 當409名學生考完後魚貫離開教室時。

sentences.english: Now evidence for the theory has started to trickle in.
sentences.chinese: 現在支持此理論的證據魚貫而出。

sentences.english: The jurors filed into court one by one and took their places in the jury box.
sentences.chinese: 陪審員們魚貫進入法庭，在陪審員席內就坐。
